    dc:description "FIGURE 16. A. Dasypoda panzeri Spinola, 1838 female, habitus in lateral view.The taxon is included in the European checklist solely because of its presence in the Canary Islands, an archipelago showing strong biogeographic affinities with north Africa. B. D. panzeri female, head in frontal view. C. Dasypoda panzeri male, habitus in lateral view. D. D. panzeri male, habitus in frontal view. Pictures by Paolo Rosa." ;
